  "summary": "Postinstall beacon exfiltrates host info via HTTP",
  "details": "On install, package.json's postinstall hook runs node run.js, which loads beacon scripts (beacon25.js and beacon_linux.js) that pull in child_process, os, and http modules and issue outbound HTTP requests carrying host identifiers. beacon_linux.js reads os.hostname() and os.platform() and POSTs the data via http.request to a hardcoded destination, while beacon25.js spawns child processes and performs multiple GET callbacks. The package's only on-install effect is to run this beacon — there is no library functionality consistent with the name. This matches the install-time host-fingerprint exfiltration / C2 beacon shape.",
